**Our client** 




 Our client is an ambitious medtech start-up developing technology at the intersection of biomarker intelligence, embedded systems, and secure infrastructure. Their mission is to enable data-driven healthcare innovation while upholding the highest standards of privacy, reliability, and data protection.




 Their multidisciplinary team spans bioengineering, data science, and product development. As they grow they are building an engineering foundation. They are looking for someone to help lead that effort with a focus on secure, private cloud infrastructure and robust systems engineering.










**The role** 




 We are looking for an
 **Head of Engineering** 
 to work closely with they
 **CTO** 
 in defining and executing the company’s technical and infrastructure strategy. This is a
 **hands-on leadership role** 
 , ideal for someone who enjoys deep technical work while maintaining a strategic view of system design and scalability.




 You’ll take responsibility for developing and maintaining the company’s
 **private cloud infrastructure** 
 , ensuring that their systems meet strict privacy, regulatory, and performance requirements. Initially, you’ll be working independently — building core systems, designing secure environments, and establishing engineering best practices — before scaling a small, high-performing team.










**Tasks & responsibilities** 



* Architect, build, and maintain the company’s private cloud infrastructure, ensuring compliance with data privacy and medical device regulations;
* Develop and optimize core systems in Rust, C, and Unix/Linux environments;
* Ensure security, resilience, and uptime across all systems, from embedded software to backend infrastructure;
* Collaborate with the CTO to define long-term engineering and infrastructure roadmaps;
* Implement modern DevOps, CI/CD, and infrastructure automation practices tailored to a private cloud environment;
* Establish and maintain strong data governance, access control, and auditability frameworks;
* Work cross-functionally with data scientists, bioengineers and product management to ensure seamless system integration;
* Contribute to a culture of technical excellence, scalability, and proactive problem-solving.









**Your profile** 



* A minimum of five years of experience in systems or infrastructure engineering, ideally in high-security or regulated environments;
* **Strong programming expertise in Rust (a must)** 
 , C, and Unix/Linux systems;
* Proven experience designing and maintaining private or on-premises cloud infrastructure (e.g., Nextcloud, OpenStack, or custom environments);
* Deep understanding of networking, security architecture, and data isolation principles;
* Hands-on experience with DevOps workflows, automation, and configuration management;
* Strategic thinker who can balance near-term delivery with long-term scalability
* Comfortable operating independently in a fast-paced start-up environment.

Flex is the diversified manufacturing partner of choice that helps market-leading brands design, build and deliver innovative products that improve the world.
A career at Flex offers the opportunity to make a difference and invest in your growth in a respectful, inclusive, and collaborative environment. If you are excited about a role but don't meet every bullet point, we encourage you to apply and join us to create the extraordinary.
Job Summary
Flex Power Modules is seeking a skilled and driven Simulation Engineer – Electronics to join our R&D team.  

In this role, you will play a key part in developing next-generation power solutions for AI datacenters and cloud infrastructure, with a focus on advanced DC/DC conversion and power electronics. You will be responsible for modeling, simulating, and validating complex electronic systems to support design decisions and research activities.
This is a unique opportunity for an engineer with strong simulation expertise and a deep understanding of power electronics who enjoys supporting designers by delivering and explaining simulation results, including the impact of potential design changes and who wants to work with cutting-edge technologies and global hyper-scalers.
What a typical day looks like:* You will work closely with our design- and advanced engineering teams;
* You will plan and estimate the time required for incoming tasks;
* You will analysis/understand the physics and the theory behind a proposed concept, figure out the way to simulate the specific task and finally demonstrate your simulation results, suggest changes and evaluate their impact;
* You will perform electromagnetic simulations using FEM tools to evaluate magnetic and PCB design, etc;
* You will perform electrical circuit simulations;
* You will perform signal integrity simulation to generate high frequency model of our board;
* You will explore new simulation methods and continuously strive to improve simulation accuracy.


The experience we’re looking to add to our team:* M.Sc. (or equivalent) in Electrical Engineering, with a focus on Power Electronics;
* Extensive experience in FEM tools like COMSOL, Ansys or CST;
* Extensive experience in electrical circuit simulations;
* Documented experience in electrical development within the field of Power Electronics;
* Fluency in English, both written and spoken.


What you’ll receive for the great work you provide:* A role at the forefront of technology in AI and data center infrastructure;
* A chance to influence product development from concept to launch;
* An innovative, international, and collaborative work environment;
* Opportunities to work with world-leading companies in cloud and tech.


